      "x": 65,
      "y": 1693,
      "width": 310,
      "height": 159,
      "text": "LOGIC:\nStep 1: Depression = Elevation (alt angles)\nStep 2: tan30° = 60/d\n  d = 60√3 = 103.92m\n\nTRICK:\nDepression from top = Elevation from bottom\nJust use tan(angle) = height/distance\nd = 60/tan30° = 60√3\n\nAnswer: 103.92 m ✓",
